original: Bäckman, Ernst Vilhelm Emanuel, ■ingenjör, Björköby, f. 15/5/91 i Vetlanda av red. Aug. B. o. Augusta Isakson. G. 17 m. Anna Grubb. Barn: Anna f. 18, Ingegärd 20, Lars 22, Ann-Marie 26, Inga-Lill 32, Gun-Britt 34. — Utex. fr. Norrköp. tekn. sk. Anst. v. Sv. Slipskive A-B Svea 10-20, A-B Vilh. Sonesson & Co. i Malmö 20, egen kvarnmaskins-, kvarnstens- o. cementvarufabr. i Björköby sed. 21. Ordf. i brandstyr., byggn :ndn o. skyt-tefören., luftsk :fogde. Medl. av Frimurarorden o. Odd Fellow. translated: Bäckman, Ernst Vilhelm Emanuel, ■engineer, Björköby, b. 15/5/91 in Vetlanda to editor Aug. B. and Augusta Isakson. Married in 1917 to Anna Grubb. Children: Anna b. 1918, Ingegärd b. 1920, Lars b. 1922, Ann-Marie b. 1926, Inga-Lill b. 1932, Gun-Britt b. 1934. — Graduated from Norrköping Technical School. Employed by Sv. Slipskive A-B Svea 1910-1920, A-B Vilh. Sonesson & Co. in Malmö from 1920, owned a mill machine, millstone and cement manufacturing company in Björköby since 1921. Chairman of the fire department, building commission and shooting club. Air raid warden. Member of the Freemason Order and Odd Fellows. Traveled to the USA in 1916-1917, Germany and Switzerland in 1938. Hobby: hunting.
